    "8) and found reliable matches between real LC responses and their corresponding model LC responses (Fig. 2d, black traces versus colour traces, and Extended Data Fig.",
    "8), yielding an average noise-corrected R 2 of approximately 0.35.",
    "This was a significant improvement over other networks with the same architecture but trained with dropout or without knockout procedures (Fig. 2e); training on behaviour was important for prediction, as these networks outperformed an untrained network (Fig.",
    "2e, untrained).",
    "The prediction performance of the 1-to-1 network was consistent with our expectations-exact matches were unlikely owing to differences in behavioural state during courtship (on which the 1-to-1 network was trained) and during imaging 11, 31."
